05/06/2007
VARNA, Bulgaria -- A joint mine-clearing drill involving the Bulgarian and Romanian militaries began in Bulgaria's Black Sea naval base in Varna on Monday (June 4th). 
The exercise is aimed at improving interoperability and co-ordination of the two countries' mine clearing units, in compliance with NATO procedures. 
It will continue until June 9th. 
(BNR, BTA - 04/06/07)
